git commit -q -m "DP2: matrix assembly + balancing

Assembled the global SFC from-whom-to-whom matrix from the 12 DP1 contracts,
pulling REAL data via the documented endpoints (no fabricated cells).

Artifacts:
- build/model/matrix_spec.json   structure-first; every cell tagged OBSERVED /
  ESTIMATED(named method) / UNVERIFIED-by-absence / HOLE; methods named before use.
- build/model/matrix_assembled.json   706 OBSERVED cells (Fed EFA 585, TIC 36
  named countries + 1 explicit residual bucket, BIS LBS 76, COFER 9 marginal).
- build/results/dp2_residual.json (verifier)   RAS/Sinkhorn run.

Honest findings (reported, not smoothed):
- The cross-border bilateral data is too sparse for a dense area-by-area RAS;
  only the TIC US-Treasury column has genuine area-by-area support. Full RAS is
  NON-CONVERGENT (row residual L2 ~ $3.96tn); largest residual sits on the US
  column. BIS claims-vs-liabilities asymmetry of 7.19% ($711bn) is an irreducible
  floor before any balancing.
- GCAP residency->nationality: the offshore USD pool is real and measured
  ($2.07tn BIS Cayman+HK; $1.94tn TIC custodial hubs); the CHINA reallocation
  magnitude is a HOLE (counterparty-nationality basis absent from the 12
  contracts). Direction upward; ~$600bn-class figure neither confirmed nor
  assumed negligible; magnitude not invented.

Integrity critic BLOCKED a false-provenance label (a build-side residual bucket
mislabeled as the publisher's All Other); fixed by retaining all 36 publisher-named
TIC countries as observed cells, so the residual now equals the publisher's true
\$710.8bn All Other (closure checks to the Grand Total within \$300mn rounding).

Oversized raw pulls (ECB QSA 226MB, Fed FWTW 76MB) gitignored as reproducible;
small processed extracts kept as evidence. Ledger: DP2 done, verifier
build/results/dp2_residual.json. DP3 not begun.

