git commit -q -m "DP1-reopen: BIS CBS (China nationality basis)

Reopened DP1 to add a 13th contract: BIS Consolidated Banking Statistics
(CBS) — the counterparty-nationality basis DP2 found missing (DP2 recorded
the China residency->nationality reallocation as a HOLE for lack of it).

Grounded against the BIS publisher, every structural claim fetched not
asserted: real dataflow WS_CBS_PUB (DSD BIS_CBS 1.0), 11-dimension order,
the CBS_BASIS/instrument/sector codelists, CN counterparty member, CSV
header, and a live observation (US banks' guarantor-basis total claims on
China, 2025-Q4 = 161,312 USD mn). Naive guesses were FALSIFIED against the
publisher and recorded as discrepancies: 'ultimate risk' is published as
'Guarantor basis' CBS_BASIS=U (not 'UR'); the 5A/position-S key returned no
results and was corrected. Integrity critic BLOCKED one ungrounded code
(L_MEASURE=S) in the headline observation; fixed by adding the CL_STOCK_FLOW
excerpt confirming S = Amounts outstanding/Stocks (a level, not a flow).

Determination: CBS-UR NARROWS but does NOT CLOSE the DP2 China HOLE. It
closes the bank-claims leg's nationality reallocation (claims consolidated
by parent-bank nationality, reallocated to ultimate obligor), but CBS covers
bank balance-sheet items only — the non-bank securities/Treasury leg (TIC/
CPIS) is out of scope, and CBS's nationality axis is the reporting bank, not
the issuer-nationality of the offshore-SPV securities pool DP2 needed.

Regenerated build/contracts/_manifest.json (13 sources). Ledger: DP1 note
updated for the reopening. DP3 not begun.

